# PFA Event Registration System

**Version 1.0** | Created by CWT1 Jack Eberhard | Last updated 1MAR2026

A fullscreen desktop application for managing Physical Fitness Assessment sign-ups. Participants register themselves through a guided form, and administrators manage days, time slots, modalities, and capacity through a password-protected panel.

---

## Requirements

- **Python 3.10 or newer** (tested on 3.14)
- **No additional packages required** — the application uses only Python standard libraries (tkinter, csv, json)
- **Runs on Windows, Unix, and MacOS

To check your Python version, open a command prompt and run:

```
python --version
```

If you do not have Python installed, download it from [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/). During installation, make sure to check **"Add Python to PATH"**.

