## Admin Panel

Access the Admin Panel by clicking the lock button on the main menu and entering the admin password. The default password is `admin2025`. The panel has six tabs:

### Overview & Stats

A dashboard showing:

- Total number of registrations
- Counts broken down by modality (Run, Swim, Bike, Treadmill, Row)
- Counts broken down by day

### All Registrations

A searchable table of every registration in the system.

- **Search** — Type in the search box (top right) to filter by any field: name, rank, event, day, time slot, etc. The table filters in real time as you type.
- **Delete** — Click a row to select it, then click the Delete button. You will be asked to confirm before the record is removed.

### Slot Capacity

A read-only overview of how full each time slot is across all days. Color-coded:

- **Green** — Under 75% full
- **Yellow** — 75% or more full
- **Red** — Completely full

Shows both the overall slot count (e.g., 15/30 total) and the breakdown by modality (e.g., Run: 8/20, Swim: 5/20).

### Manage Days

Add, rename, remove, or redate event days.

- **Add a Day** — Enter a name (e.g., "Monday") and a date (e.g., "22MAR26"), then click Add. The day will be created with the default time slots and modalities. You can have multiple days with the same name as long as the dates are different (e.g., two "Monday" entries on different weeks).
- **Edit a Day** — Change the name or date directly in the text fields for any existing day, then click Save All Changes. If you rename a day, all existing registrations for that day will be updated automatically.
- **Remove a Day** — Click the Remove button next to any day. Existing registrations for that day are preserved in the CSV but the day will no longer appear for new sign-ups.

### Manage Time Slots

Add, remove, and configure time slots, including per-slot participant caps and per-modality caps.

**Adding a new time slot:**

1. Enter the time slot in military time format (e.g., `1300-1400`)
2. Set the max participants for the slot (e.g., 30)
3. Check which days you want to add this time slot to (all are checked by default)
4. Check which modalities should be available and set the max for each. For example, if you can support 10 rowers on one day instead of the usual 6, set Row to 10.
5. Click Add Time Slot

**Editing an existing time slot:**

Click the Edit button next to any time slot to open a dialog where you can change the max participants and adjust which modalities are available and their individual caps. This lets you fine-tune capacity on a per-day, per-slot basis.

**Removing a time slot:**

Click the Remove button. The button shows how many existing registrations are in that slot. Registrations are not deleted when you remove a slot — they remain in the CSV but the slot will no longer be available for new sign-ups.

### About

Displays version information and provides the ability to **change the admin password**:

1. Enter your current password
2. Enter your new password (minimum 4 characters)
3. Confirm the new password
4. Click Update Password

The password is stored in `pfa_config.json`. If you ever forget it, you can open that file in a text editor and look for the `"admin_password"` field.

