## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| Application won't start | Make sure Python 3.10+ is installed and added to PATH. Try running `python pfa_registration.py` from a command prompt to see the error message. |
| "No module named tkinter" | Tkinter is included with standard Python on Windows. If you see this on Linux, install it with `sudo apt install python3-tk`. |
| Can't close the application | This is by design. Log into the Admin Panel and use the Exit Application button. |
| Forgot admin password | Open `pfa_config.json` in a text editor (Notepad) and find the `"admin_password"` line. |
| Data looks wrong after editing CSV manually | If you edit the CSV while the app is running, restart the app to reload the data. |
| Screen doesn't look right | The app is designed for fullscreen. Press `Alt+F4` if the display is broken, then relaunch. |
| Want to start fresh | Delete `pfa_registrations.csv` and `pfa_config.json`, then relaunch. Defaults will be recreated. |
